<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd" []>
<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="types-of-dita-documents" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:concept.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Types of DITA Documents</title>
  <conbody>
    <p id="types-of-dita-documents-intro">Serna supports DITA 1.0 and DITA 1.1 document types, as well as lets you work with <xref href="dita-specialization-serna-free.xml">DITA specializations</xref>.<note>
        <p>Although Serna supports both versions of DITA, DITA 1.0 is obsolescent . We recommend that you <xref href="creating-dita-documents-serna-free.xml">create DITA 1.1 documents</xref>.</p>
      </note></p>
    <p>The two main units of authoring in DITA are topics and maps:<ol>
        <li>
          <p><xref href="dita-topics-serna-free.xml">DITA Topics</xref></p>
          <p conref="dita-topics-serna-free.xml#dita-topics/dita-topics-definition"/>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><xref href="dita-maps-serna-free.xml">DITA Maps</xref></p>
          <p conref="map-serna-free.xml#map/dita-maps-definition"/>
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    <p>For more information, see <xref href="http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/archspec/ditamarkup.html" format="html"/>.</p>
  </conbody>
</concept>
